      "description": "<p>Instituto 12 and Leme â€“ Laboratory for Violence Reduction Host an Open Discussion on Violent Organized Crime and Public Security Policies in Rio de Janeiro and Latin America.</p><p></p><p>During the event, Joana Monteiro, director and cofounder of Leme, will interview Chris Blattman (University of Chicago), Benjamin Lessing (University of Chicago), and Carlos Schmidt-Padilla (UC Berkeley), internationally recognized experts in research on violence, organized crime, and governance in high-crime contexts.</p><p></p><p>The discussion will cover topics such as:</p><ul><li><p>What science already knows about reducing the power and violence of organized crime.</p></li><li><p>Successful experiences and the lessons they offer for the Brazilian context.</p></li><li><p>Paths to rethink public security in Rio de Janeiro and the region.</p></li><li><p></p></li></ul><p>A unique opportunity for academics, policymakers, journalists, and citizens interested in understanding, based on evidence, how to tackle one of the greatest challenges facing our city and Latin America.</p><p></p>",
